Figure 4c

Three chemokine ligands (CCL) genes were differentially expressed in public PBMC data.

library(ggplot2)
library(ggpubr)
library(cowplot)

T test and boxplots

dat<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/T1D_DE_PBMC/normalized-expressions.tsv",header=T,sep="\t")
group<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/T1D_DE_PBMC/experiment-design.tsv",header=T,row.names = 1,sep="\t")

###
CCR5<-subset(dat,Gene.Name=="CCR5" | Gene.Name=="CCL5" | Gene.Name=="CCL3" | Gene.Name=="CCL4")
CCR5<-CCR5[-c(2,3),-c(1:3)]
CCR5<-as.data.frame(t(CCR5))
names(CCR5)<-c("CCR5","CCL5","CCL4")

group<-group[rownames(CCR5),]
group=as.character(group$Sample.Characteristic.disease.)
group<-gsub(group,pattern = "type I diabetes mellitus",replacement = "T1D")

CCR5<-transform(CCR5,group=group)
CCR5$group<-factor(CCR5$group,levels = c("normal","T1D"))

p1 <- ggboxplot(data=CCR5, x="group", y="CCR5", color="group", add="jitter", short.panel.labs=F)
p1=p1 + stat_compare_means(comparisons= list(c("normal","T1D")),label="p.format",method="t.test")+theme(legend.position = "none",axis.title.x = element_blank())

p2 <- ggboxplot(data=CCR5, x="group", y="CCL5", color="group", add="jitter", short.panel.labs=F)
p2=p2 + stat_compare_means(comparisons= list(c("normal","T1D")),label="p.format",method="t.test")+theme(legend.position = "none",axis.title.x = element_blank())

p3 <- ggboxplot(data=CCR5, x="group", y="CCL4", color="group", add="jitter", short.panel.labs=F)
p3=p3 + stat_compare_means(comparisons= list(c("normal","T1D")),label="p.format",method="t.test")+theme(legend.position = "none",axis.title.x = element_blank())

plot_grid(p1,p2,p3,nrow = 1)

Figure 4e & figure 5c

Boxplot showing immune phenotype level in different genotype groups. Below is the code for figure 5c. Figure 4e was made by the same code by changing the presented SNP.

dat<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/cc_mapping/rs12778427.txt",row.names=1)
dat[1,]<-round(dat[1,])

EA<-"A"
AA<-"C"

dat<-t(dat)
dat<-as.data.frame(dat)

geno<-dat[,1]
geno<-gsub(geno,pattern="2",replacement=paste(EA,EA,sep=""))
geno<-gsub(geno,pattern="1",replacement=paste(EA,AA,sep=""))
geno<-gsub(geno,pattern="0",replacement=paste(AA,AA,sep=""))

dat[,1]<-factor(geno,levels=c(paste(EA,EA,sep=""),paste(EA,AA,sep=""),paste(AA,AA,sep="")))

names(dat)<-c("rs12778427","P")

ggboxplot(data=dat, x="rs12778427", y="P", color="rs12778427", add="jitter", short.panel.labs=F,width = 0.5)+ylab("CD45RO-CD45RA-Tcells_grandparental_percent")
